<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="promise-n">promise <strong><em>n</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /'prɒmɪs/    美 /'prɑːmɪs/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>诺言；许诺；承诺：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>his <strong>promise to</strong> his father
他对父亲的承诺</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>break / make a / one’s promise</strong>
违背诺言 / 作出承诺</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>carry out one’s promise 
履行诺言</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>keep</strong> / live up to <strong>a promise</strong>
信守诺言</p></div>

<ul>
<li>promise to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Don’t forget your promise to visit me next week. 
别忘了你答应下周来看我。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>promise + (that) 从句:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Give me your promise that you’ll never be late again. 
答应我你绝不再迟到了。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(有) 指望；(有) 前途：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Her work <strong>shows</strong> great <strong>promise</strong>. 
她的工作很有前途。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>The young man made a promise <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ his parents that he would try to earn his own living after graduation.  （2008 湖北改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. to  </p></div>